### Component: GGUF Supervisor & Optimization Flags

#### [MODIFY] [llama-cpp-supervisor.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/llama-cpp-supervisor.ts)
- Modify `spawnProcess(slot: LlamaModelSlot, ctxSize: number)` to check if `process.env.PRISM_BASE_MODE === "true"`.
- If Base Mode is enabled, enforce the following optimized spawn arguments:
  - `--threads 4`: Clamps processing exactly to the 4 physical CPU cores, bypassing context-switch scheduling bottlenecks.
  - `--batch-size 64`: Cap batch size to optimize prefill latency and reside completely within the i5 CPU's L3 cache.
  - `--ctx-size 2048`: Force clamp context windows to 2048 to prevent memory growth spikes.
  - `--flash-attn`: Force-enable flash attention arguments to decrease memory utilization.
  - `--model-draft`: Ignore slot draft settings and strip out speculative decoding parameters to avoid VRAM over-allocation.
  - `--n-gpu-layers 99`: Fully offload the small 1.5B parameters model to GTX 1050 Ti VRAM.
  - Push context state prefix caching parameters (`--grp-attn-n 1 --grp-attn-w 512`) to support instant in-memory context swaps.

