### Component: Guardian Task Catalog Pruning

#### [MODIFY] [guardian-agent.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/agents/guardian-agent.ts)
- Update `constructor` to check if `process.env.PRISM_BASE_MODE === "true"`.
- If Base Mode is engaged, filter `GUARDIAN_TASK_CATALOG` on startup, pruning all diagnostic loops and retaining only the **essential survival triad**:
  - `directive_integrity` (SHA-256 validation of instructions, run at 600,000ms)
  - `mcp_health_recovery` (Tool-server health-checking, run at 60,000ms)
  - `aab_ledger_monitor` (Infinite-loop circuit breaker, run at 30,000ms)
- Automatically disable all other tasks in `this.tasks` so that no secondary logs, system resource snapshots, or disk-checking processes consume CPU cycles on the legacy Haswell CPU.

